  "prompt": "I'm in love with my FWB, should I stop having sex with him cause every time we have sex I get more attached to him?",
  "response": "It's understandable to develop deeper feelings for someone you have a Friends with Benefits (FWB) arrangement with, especially if you\u2019re spending intimate time together. If you're noticing that the physical aspect of your relationship is intensifying your feelings and you're becoming more attached, it may be worth considering a few points:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to reflect on how you feel about him and what you want from the relationship. Are you hoping for a romantic relationship, or are you okay with the current dynamic?\n\n2. **Communicate**: If you feel comfortable, consider discussing your feelings with him. Open communication can help you understand each other's perspectives and desires.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If you decide to continue the FWB arrangement, it might be helpful to set boundaries to protect yourself emotionally. This could mean limiting physical intimacy or discussing expectations more clearly.\n\n4. **Consider Taking a Break**: If your feelings are becoming overwhelming, taking a break from the physical aspect might help you gain clarity on your emotions and what you truly want.\n\nUltimately, prioritize your emotional well-being and make choices that serve your best interests.",
